songs.description: This track is one of the most beautiful things in the world. I feel so at peace when I listen to Space 1. Have been obsessed with this song for the last two years, no signs of that changing anytime soon. I LOVE HARP MUSIC!!!
Me and Nguyen were soooooo obsessed with this track after hearing it live, it was the soundtrack to our fall. So ethereal and dreamy. The dubby bass is so good.
I started a new job in February when this album came out and my new boss and I bonded over loving this track it was sweet LOL.
When the breakbeat kicks in in the second half…. chef’s kiss. Gorgeous gentle neosoul.

songs.songname: Do You Ever D.R.E.A.M. Of Flying?
songs.description: Listening to this song is like taking a little side quest ^_^
The way this track builds is so good…there’s such a strong feeling of purpose. Killllller production.
The original track was so inspirational to me the first time I heard it, and this remix was even more so. All I can say is huge oriental vibes.
Can’t help but smile when listening to this track. Makes you feel limitless. Did a lot of biking to this track.
Found this track through Kimari and was immediately so smitten with it. SO sweet, romantic, and lovely.

Perfect groovy lil song to bop to. Heard at one of my favorite sets this year from Myles Mac and DJ Possum. Hearing this track immediately brings me to this moment surrounded by my dearest friends, so happy to be alive.
Another gorgeous dreamy track I heard at the very end of the Myles Mac and DJ Possum set. Also makes me feel similarly emo :’)

If Tinashe has a million fans, then I am one of them. If Tinashe has ten fans, then I am one of them. If Tinashe has only one fan then that is me. If Tinashe  has no fans, then that means I am no longer on earth. If the world is against Tinashe, then I am against the world.
There are so many good edits of Rain and this is definitely one of my favorites.

songs.songname: Give It Up 2 Me (Mr Carmack Remix)
songs.description: This remix is the epitome of summer. Easy breezy beautiful!
I love relistening to an old favorite album and finding a new favorite track. Another great track for biking to.
Yeah I fell for the Coke ad… bunnies rise up!!!
